{"type":"session_message","session_id":"ses_28a4be054ffe9NRt4aphiycBPg","role":"assistant","message_id":"msg_d75b4348d001ZapnREv63UT0ms","parts":[{"id":"prt_d75b43efc001x7iaTMA0ZwR2bE","messageID":"msg_d75b4348d001ZapnREv63UT0ms","sessionID":"ses_28a4be054ffe9NRt4aphiycBPg","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_74e1c3f721bf47f6afc28bba","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/index.md"},"output":"<path>/workspace/docs/index.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: # AutoML Benchmark\n2: \n3: These are the AutoML Benchmark documentation pages with information on how to\n4: configure and use the AutoML Benchmark tool. For first time users, we advise\n5: visiting the [getting started](getting_started.md) page.\n6: \n7: This documentation is accompanied by [our website](WEBSITE)\n8: which has information on [our papers](WEBSITE/papers.html),\n9: [integrated frameworks](WEBSITE/frameworks.html),\n10: and [evaluation results](WEBSITE/results.html).\n11: \n12: !!! note \"Help Wanted!\"\n13: \n14:     We recently switched to generating doc pages with `mkdocs-material`. In the process,\n15:     we did our best to make sure to use the additional functionalities to better\n16:     present the information and make it easy to find through notes, tabs, and other features.\n17: \n18:     It is possible to find parts of the documentation are not updated (correctly), or\n19:     are not clear. We welcome all help to improve the documentation. If you have a\n20:     suggestion on how to improve the documentation, please open an issue. If you find\n21:     an error, please open an issue or open a pull request directly. Thanks! :pray:\n\n(End of file - total 21 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AutoML Benchmark\n\nThese are the AutoML Benchmark documentation pages with information on how to\nconfigure and use the AutoML Benchmark tool. For first time users, we advise\nvisiting the [getting started](getting_started.md) page.\n\nThis documentation is accompanied by [our website](WEBSITE)\nwhich has information on [our papers](WEBSITE/papers.html),\n[integrated frameworks](WEBSITE/frameworks.html),\nand [evaluation results](WEBSITE/results.html).\n\n!!! note \"Help Wanted!\"\n\n    We recently switched to generating doc pages with `mkdocs-material`. In the process,\n    we did our best to make sure to use the additional functionalities to better\n    present the information and make it easy to find through notes, tabs, and other features.\n\n    It is possible to find parts of the documentation are not updated (correctly), or\n    are not clear. We welcome all help to improve the documentation. If you have a\n    suggestion on how to improve the documentation, please open an issue. If you find","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"docs/index.md","time":{"start":1775796240534,"end":1775796240545}}}]}
